# Wizard PowerShell — Codex configuration example
#
# Drop this file at C:\Users\Oleh\.codex\config.toml after reviewing.
#
# Keys not commented out below are wizard-specific. Other Codex settings (model selection,
# provider keys, sandboxing) are already managed by Codex itself; do not duplicate them here.

# Codex inherits the parent shell on Windows. When the wizard pwsh.exe shim is the user's
# default (via `Install-WizardPwsh.ps1 -RegisterAsDefault All`), Codex picks up
# WIZARD_PWSH_CONTROL=1 transparently. If a Codex tab is launched from a non-shim shell,
# the env var won't propagate.
#
# Verify in any Codex tab: ask it to run `Get-WizardSession` — the result must show
# WizardControlEnabled=$true. If it shows $false, the parent terminal isn't the wizard
# shim; relaunch through `mcp__wizard__vscode_launch_agent` or the Windows Terminal
# wizard profile.

# trusted_paths: keep this section as Codex generated it; just append the Wizard repo if you use it.
# [trusted_paths]
# "C:\\Users\\Oleh\\Documents\\GitHub\\PowerShell" = true
